### Register a new user
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "username": "user1",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Login (get access token)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Get current user (replace <TOKEN> with bearer token)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

### Create user (ADMIN) — replace <TOKEN>
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/users/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "email": "newuser@example.com",
  "username": "newuser",
  "password": "NewPass123!",
  "role": "user"
}

### List users (ADMIN) — replace <TOKEN>
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/users/
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

### Change password (owner or ADMIN) — replace <TOKEN> and {user_id}
PATCH http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/users/{user_id}/password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "new_password": "AnotherPass123!"
}

### Delete user (ADMIN) — replace <TOKEN> and {user_id}
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/users/{user_id}
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>
